      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is being used across the pharmaceutical industry, from drug discovery and clinical trials through to regulatory compliance and post-market surveillance. You will gain a clear understanding of the unique risks that arise when AI systems are applied in high risk healthcare settings, including issues around data quality, model bias, and the consequences of errors in drug development. The lesson also examines what validation means in a pharmaceutical context, and why demonstrating that an AI system is fit for purpose is essential before it can be trusted in regulated environments. By the end of this lesson, you will be better equipped to think critically about where AI adds genuine value in pharmaceuticals, and where caution, oversight, and rigorous testing are absolutely necessary.",
